# Testing Conventions

## Rules

- **Use Vitest as the test runner** and React Testing Library (RTL) for component tests. Never use Jest or Enzyme.
- **Use `renderWithRouter`** for all component renders that need routing context. This helper wraps components with the necessary providers (router, query client, i18n).
- **No CSS class assertions.** Never assert on `className`, inline styles, or CSS properties. Test behavior and DOM structure, not visual implementation.
- **Mock API calls with `nock`.** Use nock to intercept HTTP requests in tests. Never use `jest.fn()` or `vi.fn()` to mock API modules directly; mock at the network level.
- **Test user behavior, not implementation.** Use RTL queries like `getByRole`, `getByText`, `getByLabelText`. Avoid `getByTestId` unless no semantic query works.
- **Prefer `userEvent` over `fireEvent`.** `@testing-library/user-event` simulates real user interactions more accurately.
- **Each test file mirrors its source file.** `user-profile.tsx` has `user-profile.test.tsx` in the same directory.
- **Use `describe` blocks** to group related tests. Use descriptive test names that explain the expected behavior.
- **Always clean up.** nock interceptors and any side effects should be cleaned up in `afterEach`.
- **Avoid snapshot tests.** They are brittle and provide little value. Test specific behavior instead.

## Examples

### Good

```typescript
import { describe, it, expect, afterEach } from 'vitest';
import { screen, waitFor } from '@testing-library/react';
import userEvent from '@testing-library/user-event';
import nock from 'nock';

import { renderWithRouter } from '@/test-utils/render-with-router';
import { UserProfile } from './user-profile';

describe('UserProfile', () => {
  afterEach(() => {
    nock.cleanAll();
  });

  it('displays user name after loading', async () => {
    nock('http://localhost')
      .get('/api/users/1')
      .reply(200, { id: '1', name: 'Alice Johnson', email: 'alice@example.com' });

    renderWithRouter(<UserProfile userId="1" />);

    expect(screen.getByRole('progressbar')).toBeInTheDocument();

    await waitFor(() => {
      expect(screen.getByText('Alice Johnson')).toBeInTheDocument();
    });
  });

  it('shows error message when fetch fails', async () => {
    nock('http://localhost')
      .get('/api/users/1')
      .reply(500);

    renderWithRouter(<UserProfile userId="1" />);

    await waitFor(() => {
      expect(screen.getByRole('alert')).toBeInTheDocument();
    });
  });

  it('calls delete API when delete button is clicked', async () => {
    const user = userEvent.setup();
    const deleteScope = nock('http://localhost')
      .delete('/api/users/1')
      .reply(204);

    nock('http://localhost')
      .get('/api/users/1')
      .reply(200, { id: '1', name: 'Alice', email: 'alice@example.com' });

    renderWithRouter(<UserProfile userId="1" />);

    await waitFor(() => {
      expect(screen.getByText('Alice')).toBeInTheDocument();
    });

    await user.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /delete/i }));
    await user.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /confirm/i }));

    await waitFor(() => {
      expect(deleteScope.isDone()).toBe(true);
    });
  });
});
```

### Bad

```typescript
// Asserting on CSS classes
expect(button).toHaveClass('bg-primary text-white');
expect(element).toHaveStyle({ color: 'red' });

// Using fireEvent instead of userEvent
fireEvent.click(screen.getByRole('button'));

// Mocking API modules instead of network
vi.mock('@/api/users', () => ({
  getUser: vi.fn().mockResolvedValue({ name: 'Alice' }),
}));

// Using getByTestId when semantic queries work
<div data-testid="user-name">{user.name}</div>
expect(screen.getByTestId('user-name')).toHaveTextContent('Alice');
// Should be: expect(screen.getByText('Alice')).toBeInTheDocument()

// Snapshot testing
expect(container).toMatchSnapshot();

// Rendering without providers
render(<UserProfile userId="1" />); // Missing router/query/i18n providers
```
